title: Semipro football: Seven Red & Black players named EFL First Team All-Stars
text:
A A 
Seven players from the Watertown Red and Black were named to the Empire Football League All-Star First Team, highlighting 21 members of the team that received league honors. 
Quarterback Anthony Noel, running back Curtis Dukes, wide receiver Chris Furr, guard Tim Reynolds, return specialist Keegan Queior, linebacker Connor Brown, and cornerback Evan Buckingham were among the first-team selections. 
Watertown players chosen to the second team were running back Joe Brennan, offensive tackle Dan Mattner, center Avery Barney, defensive tackle Tony Ivey, defensive ends Dan Mallen and Alex Tibbles, and linebackers Rob Hughes and Tristan Jones. Offensive tackle Torrey Edwards, defensive tackle Keigan Grawbowski, defensive end Travious Webster, linebacker Heriberto Angelo, and defensive backs William Surrey and Bill Tuigamala earned honorable mention. 
The Red and Black (8-4) finished the season with a 14-6 loss to the Syracuse Strong in last Saturday’s EFL championship game at Nottingham High School. 
Syracuse running back Greg Tobias was named EFL Offensive Most Valuable Player, and Strong linebacker EJ Maeweather was selected as the league’s Defensive MVP.
